**[1865, 08-31] Ms.A.1.2.34.78A**

McKim to RDW

He has ordered *The Nation* sent to your address. “It is a paper which I
think will please you. There is no nonsense about it. … Its writers, not
being fools, don’t believe that the country is going to the Devil. The
{u}do{/u} believe, being wise men, that the good God is leading us away
from our sins, and fitting us for a great mission among the nations of
the Earth.”


